observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the LCE agreed through the Municipal Accountant, Budget and Treasurer to provide the following supporting documents for the grant of CNA incentive as identified in Section 2 of PSLMC Resolution No. 4, series of 2002, Item 4.0 of Budget Circular No. 2021-3 dated November 17, 2021, and Item 5.16 of COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012:
specific cost-cutting measures as provided in the signed CNA between the union and the Management;
proof that the funds for the incentives were taken from savings from allowable MOOE allotments as a result of cost-saving measures;
Resolution signed by both parties incorporating the guidelines/criteria for granting CNA Incentive;
Comparative statement of DBM-approved level of operating expenses and actual operating expenses;
Copy of CNA;
Certificate issued by the Head of the Agency on the total amount of encumbered savings generated form cost-cutting measures identified in the CNA which resulted from the joint efforts of labor and management and systems/productivity/income improvement;
Proof that the planned programs/activities/projects have been implemented and completed in accordance with the targets for the year.
(b)  the Municipal Accountant ensure the requisite supporting documents are complete before paying CNA grants.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant: 

(i)	require the concerned accountable officers to immediately settle their unliquidated cash advances by submitting the liquidation report and settlement documents to the Accounting Office and/or by returning the unexpended balance of the cash advance to the Municipal Treasurer;  

(ii)	discontinue the granting of cash advances to elected official other than for their official traveling expenses; 

(iii)	consider the filing of request for authority to write-off dormant unliquidated cash advance in accordance with COA Circular 2016-005, dated December 19, 2016.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
create an inventory team to conduct physical count and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and submit to COA;
require the Accounting and Treasury Office to complete their property ledger cards and conduct periodic reconciliation thereof;
require the Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Municipal Assessor and the Municipal Treasurer, to conduct an inventory of all parcels of land owned by the Municipality, and thereafter establish the correct balance of Land under Property, Plant and Equipment;
require the Municipal Accountant to prioritize the retrieval of records and supporting documents for the preparation of the Registry of Public Infrastructures, which is a supporting document to the journal entry voucher to be prepared in recording back to the appropriate asset account the public infrastructures transferred therein, and make the necessary adjustments, if warranted; and
require the Municipal accountant to make the necessary adjustments to the PPE account, correcting the errors in the recording of PPE and depreciation expense, as follows:

11.8	We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
require the concerned accountable officers to immediately settle their unliquidated cash advances by submitting the liquidation report and settlement documents to the Accounting Office and/or by returning the unexpended balance of the cash advance to the Municipal Treasurer;
discontinue the granting of cash advances to elected official other than for their official traveling expenses;
consider the filing of request for authority to write-off dormant unliquidated cash advance in accordance with COA Circular 2016-005, dated December 19, 2016.
